<?xml version='1.0' encoding='utf-8'?>
<PcGts xmlns="http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15 http://schema.primaresearch.org/PAGE/gts/pagecontent/2019-07-15/pagecontent.xsd"><Metadata><Creator>xl-export</Creator><Created>2026-03-19T00:00:00Z</Created><LastChange>2026-03-19T00:00:00Z</LastChange></Metadata><Page imageFilename="" imageWidth="1000" imageHeight="1000"><TextRegion id="r1" custom="type:paragraph"><Coords points="0,0 1000,0 1000,1000 0,1000" /><TextLine id="l1" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,0 1000,0 1000,45 0,45" /><Baseline points="0,43 1000,43" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>Peter came to me first in the autumn of his fourteenth year.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l2" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,45 1000,45 1000,90 0,90" /><Baseline points="0,88 1000,88" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>This part I can write without difficulty because I have</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l3" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,90 1000,90 1000,135 0,135" /><Baseline points="0,133 1000,133" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>written it many times in my head, the way you return to a</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l4" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,135 1000,135 1000,180 0,180" /><Baseline points="0,178 1000,178" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>place you love before it is taken from you, memorizing.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l5" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,180 1000,180 1000,225 0,225" /><Baseline points="0,223 1000,223" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>He was small for his age, dark-haired, and he held himself</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l6" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,225 1000,225 1000,270 0,270" /><Baseline points="0,268 1000,268" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>with a stillness that I recognized because I had felt it in</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l7" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,270 1000,270 1000,315 0,315" /><Baseline points="0,313 1000,313" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>myself at that age — the stillness of a person whose soul</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l8" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,315 1000,315 1000,360 0,360" /><Baseline points="0,358 1000,358" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>was moving very fast within him and who had learned to keep</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l9" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,360 1000,360 1000,405 0,405" /><Baseline points="0,403 1000,403" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>it hidden. His father was a cloth merchant. The father</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l10" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,405 1000,405 1000,450 0,450" /><Baseline points="0,448 1000,448" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>wanted him to have letters for the purpose of contracts and</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l11" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,450 1000,450 1000,495 0,495" /><Baseline points="0,493 1000,493" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>correspondence. The father was a practical man.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l12" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,495 1000,495 1000,540 0,540" /><Baseline points="0,538 1000,538" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>Within three weeks I knew that Peter was not going to be [—]</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l13" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,540 1000,540 1000,585 0,585" /><Baseline points="0,583 1000,583" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>the cloth trade. Within three months I knew he was the</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l14" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,585 1000,585 1000,630 0,630" /><Baseline points="0,628 1000,628" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>finest student I had ever taught. By spring I had stopped</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l15" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,630 1000,630 1000,675 0,675" /><Baseline points="0,673 1000,673" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>thinking of myself as his teacher in any meaningful sense</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l16" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,675 1000,675 1000,720 0,720" /><Baseline points="0,718 1000,718" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>and begun thinking of myself as the person who was currently</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l17" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,720 1000,720 1000,765 0,765" /><Baseline points="0,763 1000,763" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>standing between him and what he was going to become.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l18" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,765 1000,765 1000,810 0,810" /><Baseline points="0,808 1000,808" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I want to be careful here. I want You to see that I am being</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l19" custom="register:mixed"><Coords points="0,810 1000,810 1000,855 0,855" /><Baseline points="0,853 1000,853" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>careful.</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l20" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,855 1000,855 1000,900 0,900" /><Baseline points="0,898 1000,898" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>I did not love Peter the way a man should not love a boy. I</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l21" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,900 1000,900 1000,945 0,945" /><Baseline points="0,943 1000,943" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>want that said plainly because I am aware of how this kind</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine><TextLine id="l22" custom="register:de"><Coords points="0,945 1000,945 1000,990 0,990" /><Baseline points="0,988 1000,988" /><TextEquiv index="0"><Unicode>of account can be misread, and because the Confessions</Unicode></TextEquiv></TextLine></TextRegion></Page></PcGts>